gomodel:SYNGO_463  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Used antibodies to CaV3.2 to examine the localization of CaV3 in wild-type entorhinal cortex. The antibody to Cav3 was visualized by a silver-intensified immunogold reaction. CaV3.2 immunogold particles were present on asymmetrical synaptic terminals (Fig. 6a) in sections obtained from three wild-type mice. No CaV3.2 signal was identified on sections obtained from three CaV3.2-/- mice under either electron (Fig. 6a) or light microscopy (Supplementary Fig. 9).\n\n27/4/2017 Pim\n- Authors state: \"HCN1 and CaV3.2 colabeling was noticeable on spines and dendrites as well (Supplementary Fig. 8).\". Experimental description: Entorhinal-hippocampal slices were obtained from 8-9-week-old CaV3.2-/- and wild-type mice. Post antibody labeling, fixation and embedding, regions of interest were cut as 70-90-nm-thick sections using an ultramicrotome." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_463" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

